NAME
	proc-list (display) - render a scrollable process table joined from a status-snapshot file and a per-pid rate file, with row selection and a key-triggered kill

INTERFACE
	display (MatrixDisplay)

READS
	proc/list	one /prog/<pid>/status row per line:
			pid grpid user time state size_K module
	proc/cpurates	one line per pid: pid pct (joined onto rows by pid)

MOUNT
	The outdir of a service that produces proc/list and proc/cpurates
	- /tmp/matrix/<service>.  With sysmon-svc: /tmp/matrix/sysmon-svc.
	Include that service in the same composition (e.g.
	`service sysmon-svc /`) so its outdir is populated.

WRITES
	/prog/<pid>/ctl	the string "kill" - an ABSOLUTE path outside the
			mount, written only when the operator presses 'k'
			with a row selected

DESCRIPTION
	Columns PID/STATE/CPU%/MEM/MOD.  Button-1 toggles row selection;
	the wheel scrolls three rows.  Killing is deliberately two-step
	(select, then 'k') to prevent kill-by-misclick.  This is the one
	display module in the base set with a side effect; compositions
	that must not kill processes should not include it.

SEE ALSO
	sysmon-svc (produces proc/list and proc/cpurates in its outdir)
